                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18391125-190-offence-1 t18391125-name-955"></join>John Bradford</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18391125-name-956" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-956" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-956" type="surname" value="LANGHAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-956" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN LANGHAM</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pot-boy, in the service of George Bradford, of</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183911250137"></xptr>
               <p>the Sun and Punch-bowl public-house, High Holborn. On the morning of the 19th of November, I was cleaning up the tap-room, and the prisoner came in with another person—there were a great many pots before the tap-room fire—I saw the prisoner talking to the other man, and then go out—I suspected, and followed him to Newton-street—when he saw me he ran away—I ran after him, stopped him, and asked if he had any pots—he said he had not—I asked him to let me look at his hat—he was very loath to let me—I took it off, and found a quart-pot in it, and in his pockets two pint-pots—he said, "Pray let me go this time. "</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. There was a gentleman in the tap-room, reading the news<lb></lb>paper—I said, "Let me look at the paper, I wish to see an advertisement"—I saw the witness peeping into the tap-room—I went out, and the gentle<lb></lb>man came out, and opposite Southampton-street, he gave me the quart and one pint-pot. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. The prisoner came out first—I went after him, and while I was following him, the other ran away with more pots than the prisoner had.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18391125-name-957" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-957" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-957" type="surname" value="WOODYER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-957" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN WOODYER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I was sent for to the Sun and Punch-bowl public-house, and found the prisoner there—he said, "I had but two pots."</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
